result.execSummary:
The defendant Donald F Rick #00229807 was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide, a class A felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Restitution of $767.75 shall be paid through DOC to the Iron County District Attorney's Office to be disbursed to Ashley H.  Restitution of $5655.73 shall be paid through DOC to Security Insurance, 150 Camelot Drive, Fon du Lac, WI 54935.   Restitution shall be held open for 60 days for any additional submissions.  **Amendment**:  Restitution of $500 shall be paid through DOC to be paid to the Iron County District Attorney's Office to be disbursed to Terri B. and restitution of $30,000 shall be paid to the Iron County District Attorney's Office to be disbursed to Teresa H.  Court also orders that amount to be withheld from inmate's wages shall not exceed 60%.  **Second amendment**:  Restitution previously stated as $5655.73 to Security is corrected to $5155.73.  (Split out $500 due to Terri B.)

Defendant is sentenced to Life without possibility of ES.  Any credit for time served will be calculated by DOC.
Consecutive to: Any sentence Def is currently serving.

Defendant Donald F Rick in court with attorney Courtney J Latzig.  Richard J. Dufour appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA calls case, cites appearances.  Attorney Latzig recites potential plea to court.  Attorney Dufour agrees with Attorney Latzig's recitation and withdraws Amended Information.  Original Information stands.  Per Atty Latzig, defendant pleads guilty to Count 1.  Defendant agrees with attorney.  Freely pleads.  PLQ is filed.  Court reads elements.  Def admits signing PLQ.  No promises or threats were made to get def to sign.  Understands rights giving up.  Court questions again re threats, no threats.  Def states he would give the same answers if court asked.  Attorney Latzig is satisfied her client freely and intelligently pleads.  Court accepts plea and finds def freely pleads, finds guilty of Count #1.  Counsel request PSI.  Court orders PSI-to be done in 90 days.  State moves for DRI of other counts.  Court grants motion for DRI.  Attorney Latzig requests alternative PSI.  Court will allow.  Court orders PSI report distributed once received.  Grants defense's request for alternative PSI, if requests at time.   Attorney Latzig asks for one month for alternative PSI to be done (after original) and for def to stay in Iron County pending sentencing.  Court-def is under DOC, can't grant stay in I.C.  Court orders PSI to be done by March 8th, alternative PSI to be done by April 8th, and sentencing to be held April 13, 2017 at 1:00 p.m.  Judge understands Latzig's position on def being in I.C. and can ask for a writ to have def brought to I.C. for purposes of PSI.  Court will grant if requests.  Court orders bond to continue.  Adjourned at 2:23 p.m. klr
